A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Family Law – Children in Need of Assistance and Termination of Parental
3 Rights
4 FOR the purpose of repealing a provision that authorizes a local department of social
5 services to ask the juvenile court to find that reasonable efforts to reunify a child
6 with the child’s parent or guardian are not required if the local department concludes
7 that a parent or guardian has involuntarily lost parental rights to a sibling of the
8 child; repealing a provision that requires a court, when determining whether to
9 involuntarily terminate parental rights, to consider whether the parent has
10 involuntarily lost parental rights to a sibling of the child; and generally relating to
11 the termination of parental rights.
